data.text:
Lyubertsy, Moscow Province, Russia

Latitude and longitude coordinates are: 55.688713, 37.901073.

Lyubertsy is a large neighborhood of Moscow, locate 11 miles from Moscow city center, with the total population estimated to be 175,000 people. The settlement was established in the 17th century and after the World War II it has become one of the most developed working class community located on the very edge of the capital city of the USSR. Since the 1990s, the city is famous with being a location for smugglers and small Russian mafia clan members.
